---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/sections/CTA.astro';
---

<Layout title="Consulting — Olle Dyberg" description="AI strategy and implementation consulting. Claude Code, agents, context engineering. Let's talk before we build.">
  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="pt-32 pb-16 md:pt-40 md:pb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8">
        <div class="animate-reveal mb-10 flex items-center gap-3.5">
          <img
            src="/olle.jpg"
            alt="Olle Dyberg"
            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full object-cover border border-(--color-border)"
          />
          <p class="font-mono text-(--color-accent) text-base tracking-wide">
            Consulting
          </p>
        </div>

        <h1 class="animate-reveal delay-1 font-display text-[2.5rem] md:text-[4rem] leading-[1.05] font-normal tracking-tight mb-10">
          Let's talk before we build.
        </h1>

        <p class="animate-reveal delay-2 text-(--color-text-secondary) text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
          Every engagement starts with a conversation. I learn your stack, your team, your goals — then we figure out the right move together. Claude Code, agents, context engineering.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Services -->
    <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8">
        <hr class="rule mb-16" />

        <div class="space-y-20">
          <!-- Strategy Session -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.6fr] gap-8 md:gap-16">
            <div>
              <p class="font-mono text-sm text-(--color-muted) tracking-wide uppercase mb-2">1 hour</p>
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl tracking-tight">Strategy Session</h3>
              <p class="font-display text-xl text-(--color-accent) mt-2">€500</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-(--color-text-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                One hour, one call. We go through your current setup, identify where AI fits into your workflow, and you leave with clear, actionable next steps. No fluff, no slides.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Deep Dive — recommended -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.6fr] gap-8 md:gap-16 border-l-2 border-(--color-accent) pl-6 md:pl-8 -ml-6 md:-ml-8">
            <div>
              <p class="font-mono text-sm text-(--color-muted) tracking-wide uppercase mb-2">4 hours</p>
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl tracking-tight">Deep Dive</h3>
              <p class="font-display text-xl text-(--color-accent) mt-2">€2,000</p>
              <p class="font-mono text-sm text-(--color-accent) mt-1">Recommended</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-(--color-text-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Four hours across multiple sessions. Architecture review, hands-on guidance, and a roadmap tailored to your codebase. We go deep on Claude Code setup, agent design, and context engineering patterns.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Team Workshop -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.6fr] gap-8 md:gap-16">
            <div>
              <p class="font-mono text-sm text-(--color-muted) tracking-wide uppercase mb-2">Half day</p>
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl tracking-tight">Team Workshop</h3>
              <p class="font-display text-xl text-(--color-accent) mt-2">€3,000</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-(--color-text-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Your whole team, your actual codebase. Hands-on training in Claude Code, CLAUDE.md architecture, MCP integration, and agent workflows. Everyone walks out with muscle memory. Includes documentation and 30 days of async support.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Advisory -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.6fr] gap-8 md:gap-16">
            <div>
              <p class="font-mono text-sm text-(--color-muted) tracking-wide uppercase mb-2">Ongoing</p>
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl tracking-tight">Advisory</h3>
              <p class="font-display text-xl text-(--color-accent) mt-2">€1,500/mo</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-(--color-text-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                An AI advisor without a full-time hire. Two strategy calls per month, async support between sessions, architecture reviews, and code reviews. For teams that want ongoing expertise as they build.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Process -->
    <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8">
        <hr class="rule mb-16" />

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 md:gap-16">
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-(--color-accent) text-base mb-3">01</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl tracking-tight mb-2">We talk</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-(--color-muted) leading-relaxed">
              Email me. Tell me what you're working on. If it sounds like a fit, we book a strategy session and go from there.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-(--color-accent) text-base mb-3">02</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl tracking-tight mb-2">We scope</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-(--color-muted) leading-relaxed">
              Based on what I learn about your team and stack, I recommend the right engagement. No one-size-fits-all packages.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-(--color-accent) text-base mb-3">03</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl tracking-tight mb-2">We build</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-(--color-muted) leading-relaxed">
              Whether it's a single session or ongoing advisory, you get real output — not a deck. Documentation, async support, and follow-through.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <CTA />
  </main>
</Layout>
